# Get trader information
<%= partial 'documentation/partials/google_tag_manager_js' %>
Use the POST endpoint [Get information relating to an excise trader](/api-documentation/docs/api/service/excise-movement-control-system-api/1.0/oas/page#tag/Traders/operation/prevalidateTrader) to get information about an excise trader.

## Request body schema

Full details of the request body schema can be found in the [API reference](/api-documentation/docs/api/service/excise-movement-control-system-api/1.0/oas/page#tag/Movements/operation/prevalidateTrader).

The request body must include the excise reference number (ERN), entity group and authorisation request.

### Entity groups

The following entity groups are available:

- UK Record
- EU Trader
- EU Warehouse
- EU Temporary Authorisation

## Responses 

Full details of successful and unsuccessful responses and their schema can be found in the [API reference](/api-documentation/docs/api/service/excise-movement-control-system-api/1.0/oas/page#tag/Movements/operation/prevalidateTrader) on the HMRC Developer Hub.

| Response code | Status | Details | Contents | 
| -- | -- | -- | -- |
| 200 | Successful | Validation performed successfully | validation timestamp, ERN, entity group, valid trader, trader type, validate product authorisation response |
| 200 | Successful | Validation performed with a business error (invalid trader, invalid product codes) | validation timestamp, ERN, entity group, valid trader, error code, error text, trader type, validate product authorisation response |
| 400 | Unsuccesful| Invalid JSON or mandatory fields missing | DateTime, message, debug message |
| 500 | Unsuccessful | Internal server error | DateTime, message, debug message |

### Trader types

The following trader types are available:

1. Warehouse Keeper
2. Tax Warehouse
3. Registered Consignor
4. Registered Consignee
5. Temporary Registered Consignee
6. Temporary Registered Authorisation
7. Other